---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const siteOrigin = (Astro.site ?? new URL('https://jabrahamtech.com')).toString().replace(/\/$/, '');
const personId = `${siteOrigin}/#jonathan`;
const url = `${siteOrigin}/about`;

const profileJsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'ProfilePage',
  '@id': `${url}#profile`,
  url,
  name: 'About Jonathan Abraham',
  inLanguage: 'en',
  mainEntity: { '@id': personId },
  about: { '@id': personId },
};

const description = "Jonathan Abraham — I build AI products from messy idea to shipped system. Voice agents, backend services, workflow design. Technical founder at Brokerloop, Melbourne.";
---
<Base
  title="About — Jonathan Abraham"
  description={description}
  pageType="profile"
  jsonLd={profileJsonLd}
>
  <main id="content" class="wrap">
    <header class="page-head">
      <h1 class="prompt"><span class="ph-prefix eng-only">./</span>about</h1>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <header class="bio-head" aria-hidden="false">
        <figure class="avatar">
          <img src="/about/avatar.jpeg" alt="Jonathan Abraham" width="200" height="200" loading="eager" />
        </figure>
        <div class="bio-head-text paper-only">
          <p class="bio-name">Jonathan Abraham</p>
          <p class="bio-role">AI product engineer · technical founder, Brokerloop · Melbourne, AU</p>
          <ul class="bio-contact">
            <li><a href="mailto:jabrahamtech@gmail.com">Email</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/jabrahamtech" target="_blank" rel="me noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jabrahamtech" target="_blank" rel="me noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </header>

      <p class="lede">I'm Jonathan. I build AI products from messy idea to shipped system.</p>

      <p>For the past five years I have been building production systems. For the last two, most of that work has been in AI: voice agents, intake automation, long-form workflows, backend services, and the integrations those systems need to survive outside a demo.</p>

      <p>Most recently, I have been building at <strong>Brokerloop</strong>, a Melbourne-based Australian insurtech, as technical founder. The work there has been practical by necessity: voice intake, broker workflows, Go services, compliance constraints, real customers, and integrations people actually use.</p>

      <p>I came into AI through full-stack engineering and consulting, not research. That route shapes how I think. Before asking which model to use, I care about what should be built, who it is for, what it costs, what breaks, what needs human review, and what metric proves it is useful.</p>

      <p>The model is one piece of the system, not the system.</p>

      <p>This site is mostly notes from that work: AI product direction, voice AI, backend systems, Go, workflow design, production lessons, and the gap between impressive demos and products people actually adopt.</p>

      <p>Outside my main work, I take a small number of contracts each year. I am most useful to teams with an AI prototype that works in a demo but needs clearer product direction, stronger backend infrastructure, workflow design, or production hardening.</p>

      <p><strong>New work is usually by referral.</strong> Email is the easiest way to reach me: <a href="mailto:jabrahamtech@gmail.com">jabrahamtech@gmail.com</a>.</p>

      <h2>Selected work</h2>
      <p class="work-frame">Mostly greenfield — small startup builds through to large production systems. Confidential where noted.</p>
      <ul class="work-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Fraud detection AI · tier-one Australian bank.</strong>
          Architected an AI fraud-detection system inside one of the big four. Internal-facing, regulated environment, lived inside the bank's stack with all the audit trail that implies. Confidential client.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>US engineering contract · funded LA startup (2024).</strong>
          Helped a Los Angeles company ship their first venture-backed product. Shipped engineering across the time gap. Confidential. Open to more US work.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Brokerloop · technical founder.</strong>
          I run this. Voice intake for Australian insurance brokers, plus the Go services underneath — integrations with broker platforms, long-form workflows, and the parts that have to keep working when call volume spikes.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>IoT automation · largest laundry in the southern hemisphere.</strong>
          Built the automation layer connecting industrial machines to operations. Real machines on a real floor, throughput at scale, runs hands-off. Range work — proves the engineering travels outside AI.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Low-latency event-driven architecture.</strong>
          A sub-second decision pipeline I originally built around prediction markets. The architecture works anywhere reaction time is the bottleneck: trading signals, real-time risk, anything event-driven.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Open source · what I'm reading.</strong>
          I read more code than I write publicly. Currently following <a href="https://github.com/nautechsystems/nautilus_trader" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">nautilus_trader</a> (Rust trading engine), <a href="https://github.com/comfyanonymous/ComfyUI" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ComfyUI</a> (diffusion graph), and <a href="https://github.com/open-webui/open-webui" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">open-webui</a> (local LLM tooling).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
      <ul class="elsewhere-list">
        <li><strong>email</strong> — <a href="mailto:jabrahamtech@gmail.com">jabrahamtech@gmail.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>github</strong> — <a href="https://github.com/jabrahamtech" target="_blank" rel="me noopener noreferrer">/jabrahamtech</a></li>
        <li><strong>linkedin</strong> — <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jabrahamtech" target="_blank" rel="me noopener noreferrer">/in/jabrahamtech</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <div class="ascii-div" aria-hidden="true">━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━</div>
  </main>
</Base>
